<h2>Insurance</h2>

<p>Once you sign up for a health insurance policy in Berlin, you receive an Insurance Card, which you have to present when seeking medical attention at a doctorâ€™s office or hospital. Health insurance covers the majority of your basic medical needs, and it is usually all you need. </p>


<% income_range = 88000 %>
<% employment_status = "employed" %>
<% age = 30 %>


<% if income_range < 62550 || (employment_status == "student" && age < 30)  %>
    <h3>Based on your WAY answers you should have public health care.</h3>
    <p>Please select from the following public health care options below:</p>


        <ul>
            <% @public_insurances.each do |insurance| %>
            <li><%=insurance.name %></li>
            <p><%= insurance.summary %></p>
            <% end %>
        </ul>

    <% elsif age <= 35 && income_range > 62550 %>

    <h3>Based on your WAY answers you should have private health care as it is cheaper in the long term.</h3>
    <p>Please select from the following private health care options below:</p>

        <ul>
            <% @private_insurances.each do |insurance| %>
            <li><%=insurance.name%></li>
            <p><%= insurance.summary %></p>
            <% end %>
        </ul>

    <% else %>

      <h3>Based on your WAY answers you could have either public or private health insurance.</h3>
      <p>Please select from the following private health care options below:</p>

      <%# Or display another question like in the WAY from asking where theyd like public or private and maybe show a comparison
      then either display public or private instead of all as below %>

        <ul>
            <% @insurances.each do |insurance| %>
            <li><%=link_to insurance.name, insurance_path(insurance) %></li>
            <% end %>
        </ul>

    <% end %>





